      "message": "The spec does not say anything about memory slots - that\u0027s a compiler optimization. The spec says that each time you declare a variable you get a fresh variable. If the compiler puts the variable from multiple iterations in the same memory slot in a way that they don\u0027t all look like distinct variables, that\u0027s a compiler bug. See also \nhttps://golang.org/doc/faq#closures_and_goroutines. If you want to discuss further, this code review is not the right forum. See golang.org/wiki/Questions.",
